%20450%20metres%2C%20will%20pass%20within%2037%2C000%20km%20of%20Earth%20%E2%80%93%20it%20might%20be%20visible%20to%20the%20naked%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fcollisions-could-increase-chance-apophis-hitting-earth%C2%A0%5C%22%3ENew%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20that%20if%20smaller%20asteroids%20or%20space%20rocks%20were%20to%20collide%20with%20Apophis%2C%20they%20could%20potentially%20alter%20its%20trajectory.%20The%20implications%20of%20this%20are%20significant.%20Although%20Apophis%20is%20nearly%20as%20wide%20as%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20is%20tall%2C%20such%20collisions%20might%20redirect%20its%20path%2C%20possibly%20affecting%20future%20encounters%20with%20Earth%2C%20including%20its%202029%20flyby.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20has%20been%20keeping%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20asteroid%20Apophis.%20Earlier%2C%20ISRO's%20Chairman%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fapophis-asteroid-isros-newest-headache-how-to-ward-off-egyptian-god-of-chaos-6530873%5C%22%3EDr%20S%20Somanath%20told%20NDTV%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20large%20asteroid%20strike%20posed%20a%20%E2%80%9Creal%20existential%20threat%20to%20humanity%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CISRO%20is%20very%20alive%20to%20that%20threat%20and%20our%20Network%20for%20Space%20Objects%20Tracking%20and%20Analysis%20(NETRA)%20is%20monitoring%20Apophis%20very%20closely.%20After%20all%2C%20we%20have%20only%20one%20Earth%20to%20live%20on.%20India%20will%20cooperate%20with%20all%20nations%20to%20ward%20off%20this%20and%20other%20such%20future%20threats%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20ISRO%20Chairman%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20new%20research%20by%20astronomer%20Paul%20Wiegert%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Western%20Ontario%20indicates%20the%20odds%20of%20Apophis%20being%20deflected%20onto%20a%20collision%20course%20with%20Earth%20by%20smaller%20asteroids%20are%20slim.%20According%20to%20Wiegert%2C%20the%20probability%20of%20an%20asteroid%20collision%20shifting%20Apophis%20onto%20a%20dangerous%20path%20is%20about%201%20in%201%20million%2C%20with%20the%20chance%20of%20a%20direct%20impact%20in%202029%20being%201%20in%202%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWiegert's%20study%20stated%20that%20while%20small%20asteroids%20hitting%20Apophis%20could%20theoretically%20alter%20its%20trajectory%2C%20such%20events%20are%20highly%20improbable%2C%20reported%20Space.com.%20The%20research%20evaluated%20potential%20impacts%20from%20objects%20ranging%20in%20size%20from%2060%20centimetres%20to%203%20metres%2C%20revealing%20that%20these%20collisions%20would%20need%20to%20occur%20at%20precise%20angles%20to%20affect%20Apophis's%20path%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiscovered%20in%202004%2C%20Apophis%20initially%20raised%20alarm%20due%20to%20its%20size%20and%20route%2C%20making%20it%20a%20significant%20concern%20on%20impact%20risk%20lists%20by%20both%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20(ESA)%20and%20NASA.%20However%2C%20a%20close%20flyby%20in%20March%202021%20reassured%20scientists%20that%20Apophis%20would%20not%20pose%20a%20threat%20for%20at%20least%20the%20next%20100%20years.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnDespite%20its%20menacing%20nickname%2C%20the%20asteroid's%20upcoming%20approach%20in%202029%20is%20unlikely%20to%20result%20in%20a%20catastrophic%20collision.%20Should%20future%20passages%20in%202036%20or%202068%20show%20any%20threat%2C%20scientists%20have%20discussed%20potential%20mitigation%20strategies%2C%20including%20deflection%20missions%20similar%20to%20NASA's%20Double%20Asteroid%20Redirection%20Test%20(DART).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726653000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fun15ft5k_asteroid-generic_625x300_06_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fasteroid-apophis-massive-asteroids-near-earth-approach-in-2029-but-theres-a-bigger-danger-6592339%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2